---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import { href } from '../lib/url';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Why Floor Life exists: to marry the science of floor living with the beauty of it, honestly, for the ordinary Western home."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="The story & the method"
    title="About Floor Life"
    lede="Two camps already write about living close to the ground. One has the evidence and none of the charm. The other has all the charm and skips the evidence. We're trying to stand in the gap."
  />

  <div class="prose prose-floor mx-auto mt-12 max-w-2xl px-5 pb-8 sm:px-8">
    <p>
      On one side sit the movement people — biomechanists and mobility coaches
      with credible, sometimes viral science, wrapped in plain, functional,
      faintly clinical writing. On the other sit the design people — beautiful
      photography of tatami rooms and low sofas, treating the floor as a styling
      trend and rarely mentioning why it might matter.
    </p>
    <p>
      Floor Life is an attempt to hold both at once: the calm, sunlit beauty of a
      home built low to the ground, <em>and</em> an honest account of what the
      research actually says — applied not to a Japanese farmhouse but to an
      ordinary Western apartment with a couch and a deadline.
    </p>

    <h2>What we believe</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Honesty is the whole brand.</strong> Every strong claim gets its
        caveat. When the evidence is thin, we say so. Being trusted is worth more
        than sounding impressive.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Retrofit, don't evangelise.</strong> You don't have to go
        furniture-free. One inviting corner beats a vow you'll break by Thursday.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Variety over dogma.</strong> There is no single correct posture.
        The goal is to own many and move between them — which also happens to be
        the safest way to treat your joints.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Beauty is functional.</strong> A floor you want to be on is a
        floor you'll use. Charm isn't decoration here; it's the mechanism.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who it's for</h2>
    <p>
      The floor-curious taking their first cushion down, and the seasoned
      floor-sitter going deeper. Start with <a href={href('/why')}>the evidence</a>,
      or just <a href={href('/start')}>get down on the floor</a> and see how it
      feels.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-inkmuted">
      Not medical advice — see the <a href={href('/disclosure')}>disclosure</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
